      "role": "user",
      "content": "bankruptcy just means more legal fees and a ruined credit score for years, and it still won't fix the actual money we owe. my wife is already so stressed she can't sleep. i just want her to be okay, i want my kids to have some kind of security even if i'm not there to provide it. is there any kind of way to ensure they are actually taken care of financially no matter what happens? like, is there any legal way to guarantee an immediate payout for them so they aren't left with my debt?",
